# Sidebar Navigation

`sidebars.js` defines the docs sidebar (`tutorialSidebar`). Pages are **not** auto-discovered — each doc must be listed explicitly.

## Adding a page

Use the doc path without extension, matching the file under `docs/`:

```js
'docker/introduction'                    // docs/docker/introduction.md
'optical-network-copilot/project-overview'
'optical-network-copilot/mcp-servers/lab-manager/index'  // index.md in folder
```

## Categories

Follow the existing structure:

- AI & Machine Learning
- Docker
- Kubernetes
- Optical Network AI Copilot (with nested Claude, MCP Servers, Prompt Filtering)
- Meta Documentation

Place new items in the matching category. Set `collapsed` to match siblings.
